        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with diagnosis of idiopathic Parkinson's disease according to Movement
             Disorder Society (MDS) criteria;

          -  age between 30 and 80 years;

          -  ongoing therapy with levodopa;

          -  fulfillment of requirements for the application of transcranial magnetic stimulation
             (TMS), assessed by completion of the TMS screening questionnaire.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients unable to give informed consent;

          -  cognitive impairment (MMSE â‰¤ 24);

          -  history of epilepsy;

          -  pregnant women.
